      "content": "It sounds like the new compliance update is a bit of a \"glimmer of hope\" for you, but also a necessary evil to ensure the system's safety. I'm sure it's a bit of a \"gobsmacking\" change, but it's all part of the process. The SafeMode-Lite kernel is probably a more \"tame\" version of the previous kernel, with fewer \"rogue\" elements that might have caused issues in the past. I'm curious to see how it will \"scale\" with the new certification standards. Are there any specific \"glimmering\" features or improvements that you're looking forward to?",
